parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unable to view important information such as fuel levels, mileage, and maintenance warnings, which can lead to safety issues such as running out of fuel or being unaware of necessary maintenance.
symptoms: The instrument cluster display is blank or shows gibberish
the fuel gauge and odometer are not displaying correctly
the display is flickering or scrambled
and the vehicle's mileage and maintenance information are not accessible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to be unaware of the fuel level, leading to the risk of running out of fuel and causing an accident or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge is not displaying correctly
the fuel gauge is blank or showing gibberish
and the driver is unable to determine the fuel level.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the odometer can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's mileage, leading to the risk of missing necessary maintenance and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: The odometer is not displaying correctly
the odometer is blank or showing gibberish
and the driver is unable to determine the vehicle's mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose acceleration, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may jerk or shudder
lose power
or fail to accelerate
with warning lights illuminating on the dashboard. In some cases
the transmission may completely fail
leaving the vehicle unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience electrical system issues
such as the failure of the starter
alternator
or battery
leading to difficulty starting the vehicle or loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle beam assembly can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience issues with the rear axle beam assembly
such as bending or misalignment
leading to problems with the front end alignment and potential loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VTC actuator can cause the engine to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience issues with the VTC actuator
such as a grinding sound on startup
which can lead to catastrophic failure of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Variable Valve Timing Control (VTC) Actuator Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VTC actuator can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Occasional rattling noise at cold-start
loud rattling noise when starting the engine
loss of power
smoke
and engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injectors can cause the engine to misfire, leading to loss of power, stalling, and accidents.
symptoms: Engine misfire
rough idling
loss of power
check engine light
and stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter can cause the engine to fail to start, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Difficulty starting the engine
engine failure to start
and loud grinding noise when starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine splash guard can cause a road hazard, leading to accidents or damage to other vehicles.
symptoms: Plastic engine splash guard comes loose and drags on the road
making a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
